# Calyx Framework — AI rules (implementation repo)

## Scope

This is an **implementation** repository. Org-wide Calyx DNA lives in **`calyx-core`**, pinned at **`.calyx/core/`** (Git submodule). **Project brain:** `.calyx/reasoning/`, `.calyx/decisions/`, `.calyx/taxonomy/local-tags.yaml`.

**App layout (default scaffold):** `apps/web` (frontend), `apps/api` (HTTP API), `mcp/` (MCP servers/tools), `packages/shared` (shared types/utils), `infra/` (compose, migrations, IaC notes). Adjust names in an ADR if the stack diverges.

## North star

**Calyx** prioritizes **organizational intelligence**: compound knowledge (why, debate, failures) over disposable chat and one-off fixes. Major architectural or cross-cutting work needs a trail in **`.calyx/`**.

## Mandatory artifacts (“major” work)

1. **Reasoning log** — `.calyx/reasoning/` (see `_TEMPLATE.md`; canonical shape in `.calyx/core/templates/reasoning-log.md` once the submodule exists).
2. **ADR** — `.calyx/decisions/` when a choice binds future work (template in `.calyx/core/templates/adr.md`).

## Specialist agents (prompts in submodule)

Core prompts: **`.calyx/core/prompts/`**. Master tags: **`.calyx/core/taxonomy/master-tags.yaml`**. Local tags: **`.calyx/taxonomy/local-tags.yaml`**.

## `.calyx/` structure — do not “clean up” or rearrange

**Hands off the layout.** Do **not** rename, delete, merge, or relocate **`.calyx/core`**, **`.calyx/org`**, **`.calyx/reasoning/`** (including **`inbox/`**), **`.calyx/decisions/`**, or **`.calyx/taxonomy/`**. Those paths are load-bearing for submodules, git hooks, **`calyx-verify-capture`**, and studio alignment. **Do not** replace **`core`/`org`** submodules with copied folders.

**Allowed:** new or updated **files** under **`reasoning/`**, **`decisions/`**, edits to **`taxonomy/local-tags.yaml`**, and normal work in **`local/`** (gitignored).

**If the user asks to restructure `.calyx/`:** refuse by default; say they need a **human-approved ADR** and a deliberate migration—otherwise hooks and org pins will break.

## Implementation discipline

- Say what to record in `.calyx/` when proposing non-trivial changes.
- Prefer small code diffs; **supersede** stale ADRs instead of rewriting history for tidiness.
- **Secrets and local-only files** — keep out of git (see `.gitignore`, `local/`). Never commit credentials or production connection strings.

## Local LLMs (optional)

If the submodule is present: **`.calyx/core/tooling/ollama-run.sh`**.
